      "outcome": "The Wardens pull back from their exposed canal approach position, ending the commercial blockade of the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier. The Signal-House Families' gondola traffic resumes unimpeded, and the \"doubly authenticated\" service expands rapidly. However, the Wardens' consolidation strengthens their defensive position at Tower Bridge Concourse — the garrison is no longer split, and the checkpoint's fortifications are reinforced. Market informants report that the Shrine Auditors' Council is internally divided over the Silent Spire consecration, and that the Lacquer Authority's agents were granted supervised archive access that may have overstepped its bounds. The Wardens begin building a dossier of their own — not on the Families, but on the Council's vulnerabilities. The legitimacy crisis persists, but the Wardens stabilize their revenue by focusing on operators who still recognize secular tariff authority. The Canal Market District's waterways are no longer contested by Warden guards, but the political battle for message-route permits has only intensified.",
      "targetLocation": "Tower Bridge Concourse",
