      "outcome": "The Shrine Auditors' Council dispatches a corps of twelve shrine auditors to the Seal Verification Chamber under emergency liturgical authority. The auditors discover that the Lacquer Authority's agents copied at least seven high-value consecrated seal templates during their supervised access — templates that could be used to forge authenticated message routes. The Council immediately revokes the Authority's access, re-consecrates all exposed seal matrices with new cryptographic wards, and posts permanent auditor guards at the archive entrance. A formal protest is filed against the Lacquer Authority for \"exceeding the bounds of supervised reference access,\" though the Council stops short of declaring the licensing treaty void — they cannot afford to alienate the Signal-House Families while the Wardens remain a threat. The audit also reveals that the Council's own bureaucratic oversight was lax during the original access grant, a vulnerability the Wardens' informants will likely exploit. The Council tightens internal protocols, requiring dual-auditor supervision for all future external access to consecrated materials.",
      "targetLocation": "Seal Verification Chamber",
