      "outcome": "The licensing treaty is signed at the Resin Mixing Chamber under heavy security. The Signal-House Families agree to a 30% revenue share on all premium authentication services in exchange for exclusive access to the Authority's sealant formula and the new \"Triply Authenticated\" standard. The Families' gondola operators and Night Courier Depot now route all high-value messages through Authority-certified channels. The Shrine Auditors' Council, learning of the arrangement through their own informants, is alarmed — the Authority has effectively created a parallel authentication system using stolen consecrated templates, but the Council cannot prove the templates were used without revealing the extent of their own security failure. The Guild Wardens, still pinned at Tower Bridge Concourse, watch their remaining tariff revenue evaporate as operators flock to the superior authentication service. The Authority's monopoly takes root.",
